                    <p>Hence we have a paradox of stress and immunity &mdash; stress hormones (glucocorticoid) enhances immunity in the short term and suppresses immunity in the longer term &mdash; and when that balance is disrupted, we are in trouble. Research shows that transient stressors (lots of short phases A and B ) increase the risk of autoimmunity, while chronic stress brings you to phase C, suppressed immunity.</p>
